The paper deals with the problem of compressive hyperspectral imaging reconstruction, which involves signal processing, image processing, and information theory. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely category. The paper also involves iterative algorithms and denoising techniques, which are related to cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.SP (Signal Processing). The paper also deals with numerical experiments, which are related to cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper involves applications in natural sciences, which are related to cs.OH (Other Computer Science).
